Package: stackgbm
Title: Stacked Gradient Boosting Machines
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nan", "Xiao", email = "me@nanx.me", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0250-5673")))
Description: A minimalist implementation of model stacking
    by Wolpert (1992) <doi:10.1016/S0893-6080(05)80023-1>
    for boosted tree models built by
    'xgboost' <doi:10.1145/2939672.2939785>,
    'lightgbm' <https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.5555/3294996.3295074>,
    and 'catboost' <https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.5555/3327757.3327770>.
    A classic, two-layer stacking model is implemented, where the first layer
    generates features using gradient boosting trees, and the second layer
    employs a logistic regression model that uses these features as inputs.
    It aims to provide a simple and efficient way to combine multiple gradient
    boosting models to improve predictive model performance and robustness.
